While initial information indicated that two men were trapped on the crane near the Boardwalk Inkwazi Shopping Centre it has since emerged that it was just one man in the crane - and that it was not a hostage situation as initially reported to SAPS and rescue services.IPSS Medical Rescue paramedic Richard Schouten who was on the scene confirmed that the man had agreed to come down with the assistance of rescue teams. Over and done. Single person safe on ground in SAPS custody said Schouten.The man is being questioned by police. TMG Digital/The Times